other_tests.findings: Malignant cells consistent with metastatic melanoma.

Erythematous, edematous, and purulent-appearing mucosa in the terminal ileum; discontinuous areas of patchy inflamed colonic mucosa; scattered clean-based ulcers, particularly severe on the right side of the colon and in the cecum.
Normal cell count, normal protein level, negative Gram staining and culture, negative cytologic examination.
Motor axonal neuropathy affecting the arms and legs, with relative sparing of sensory function.
Bronchoalveolar lavage positive for Aspergillus flavus.
